quran[39]{c,v,t}:
  23,36,"Away, away with that you are promised"
  23,37,"There is nothing but our present life; we die, and we live, and we shall not be raised up"
  23,38,"He is naught but a man who has forged against God a lie, and we will not believe him"
  23,39,"He said, 'O my Lord, help me, for that they cry me lies"
  23,40,"He said, 'In a little they will be remorseful"
  23,41,"And the Cry seized them justly, and We made them as scum; so away with the people of the evildoers"
  23,42,"Thereafter, after them, We produced other generations"
  23,43,"no nation outstrips its term, nor do they put it back"
  23,44,"Then sent We Our Messengers successively; whenever its Messenger came to a nation they cried him lies, so We caused some of them to follow others, and We made them as but tales; so away with a people who do not believe"
  23,45,Then We sent Moses and his brother Aaron with Our signs and a manifest authority
  23,46,"unto Pharaoh and his Council; but they waxed proud, and they were a lofty people"
  23,47,"and they said, 'What, shall we believe two mortals like ourselves, whose people are our servants"
  23,48,"So they cried them lies, and they were among the destroyed"
  23,49,"And We gave Moses the Book, that haply they would be guided"
  23,50,"and We made Mary's son, and his mother, to be a sign, and gave them refuge upon a height, where was a hollow and a spring"
  23,51,"O Messengers, eat of the good things and do righteousness; surely I know the things you do"
  23,52,"Surely this community of yours is one community, and I am your Lord; so fear Me"
  23,53,"But they split in their affair between them into sects, each party rejoicing in what is with them"
  23,54,So leave thou them in their perplexity for a time
  23,55,"What, do they think that We succour them with of wealth and children"
  23,56,"We vie in good works for them? Nay, but they are not aware"
  23,57,Surely those who tremble in fear of their Lord
  23,58,and those who believe in the signs of their Lord
  23,59,and those who associate naught with their Lord
  23,60,"and those who give what they give, their hearts quaking that they are returning to their Lord"
  23,61,"those vie in good works, outracing to them"
  23,62,"We charge not any soul save to its capacity, and with Us is a Book speaking truth, and they shall not be wronged"
  23,63,"Nay, but their hearts are in perplexity as to this, and they have deeds besides that that they are doing"
  23,64,"Till, when We seize with the chastisement the ones of them that live at ease, behold, they groan"
  23,65,Groan not today; surely you shall not be helped from Us
  23,66,"My signs were recited to you, but upon your heels you withdrew"
  23,67,"waxing proud against it, talking foolish talk by night"
  23,68,"Have they not pondered the saying, or came there upon them that which came not upon their fathers, the ancients"
  23,69,Or did they not recognise their Messenger and so denied him
  23,70,"Or do they say, 'He is bedevilled'? Nay, he has brought them the truth, but most of them are averse from the truth"
  23,71,"Had the truth followed their caprices, the heavens and the earth and whosoever in them is had surely corrupted. Nay, We brought them their Remembrance, but from their Remembrance they turned"
  23,72,"Or dost thou ask them for tribute? Yet the tribute of thy Lord is better, and He is the best of providers"
  23,73,Assuredly thou art calling them to a straight path
  23,74,and surely they that believe not in the world to come are deviating from the path